# SQL Conventions

## File Naming
- Init scripts are numbered in execution order: `01_`, `02_`, `03_`, etc.
- These run automatically when the Postgres container starts for the first time

## Table Naming
- Always schema-qualified: `schema.table_name` (e.g. `silver.transactions`)
- Snake_case for all identifiers

## Standards
- Grant privileges to `teodor_admin` after creating tables

## Schema Roles
- `staging`: temporary, uses DROP IF EXISTS + CREATE (rebuilt each run)
- `bronze`: permanent raw archive, append-only
- `silver`: cleaned data with `transaction_hash UNIQUE` for deduplication
- `metadata`: pipeline logs and audit trails
